  <para>
    A <link
    linkend="Section-Graphics-LayerSet"><classname>LayerSet</classname></link>
    is a collection of graphics <link
    linkend="Section-Graphics-Layer"><classname>Layers</classname></link>,
    each displaying some aspect the same object.  The displayable
    objects are things like &micros;, &skels; and &meshes;.  Each
    <classname>Layer</classname> has a single <xref
    linkend="RegisteredClass-DisplayMethod"/>, which determines how
    the object is drawn in the <link
    linkend="Chapter-Graphics">Graphics window</link>.
  </para>
  <para>
    The <command>OOF.LayerEditor.LayerSet</command> menu contains
    commands for manipulating <classname>LayerSets</classname>.  It is
    where <classname>Layers</classname> are created and added to
    <classname>LayerSets</classname>, and where
    <classname>LayerSets</classname> are sent to Graphics windows.
  </para>


